Title: The LEGO Batman Movie Official Comic-Con Trailer (2017) - Will Arnett Movie
Comment:
Just watched this movie and it is absolutely amazing. 

The jokes and the way the movie brings up serious topics and shows batman reflecting on himself and becoming a better person I loved. I could really relate to his situation and I think the movie overall was not only entertaining all the way through but also helped me reflect on how I myself might distance myself from feelings especially. 
This movie shows that though feelings may be painful, you shouldnt push them away and avoid them. It is part of life. I really think the messages portrayed to the audience in this movie are excellent and well done! 

Great movie, I recommend watching it, even for adults whom I actually think the jokes in this movie are aimed at. (Among the jokes, the quotes in this movie are also amazing.)

Title: The LEGO Batman Movie Official Comic-Con Trailer (2017) - Will Arnett Movie
Comment: Yes this does look awesome, but what I don't understand is why people keep saying this looks better than the upcoming DC movies... This is a spoof on the comics, in a very similar way like how the 60's movie and tv show were a spoof making fun of the affects of the comics code placed upon dc comics which severely handicapped the batman books.  Batman's stories all tend to be VERY dark, I mean dark like he walks into a room and their is body strung up in pieces and someone is eating it dark.  And for that matter the DC AND Marvel comics tend to have very serious stories.  Captain America Civil War was a joke compared to the actual graphic novel.  The stakes were high, people died and at the end of the day one of the titular characters was dead and the other was a broken man.  The comic in comic book does not stand for comedy.  These stories aren't written for children, they are tales of America's modern mythology.  Superman is our modern day Achilles and Batman is our odysseus. Yes Batman v superman the theatrical version had problems, the ultimate cut should have been what was released, but demanding that every other line be funny is completely out of character for some of the heroes in both the DC and Marvel comics.  Not to say someone can't crack a joke, but I don't remember Captain America ever making wise cracks while Manhattan was getting destroyed by the masters of evil.

Title: The LEGO Batman Movie Official Comic-Con Trailer (2017) - Will Arnett Movie
Comment: Ok, I've been saying all of this time that I thought that casting Michael Cera as Dick Grayson, (my favorite DC character) was a horrible idea since I personally think he's a really bad actor. I loved Scott Pilgrim, but his performance in that film was atrocious. And the released pictures didn't help either, it looked like they aboslutely ruined him. However this trailer showcases that acting and voice acting are not the same thing, Michael Cera sounds fantastic in this trailer, showing a range that I didn't even know he had. Get rid of the stupid glasses and give him black hair and perfect (Ok not perfect, I wish that he had the lego new 52 Robin costume, but I digress). Really pleasantly surprised. I hope that in a sequel maybe Batman, Alfred and Batgirl get ready to celebrate his 13th birthday and as the clock strikes 12, he automatically switches into his moody teenager mode and becomes Nightwing.
